📄 Part 5 – Advanced Features, Enhancements and Final System Summary


---

1. Introduction

This section describes the advanced capabilities, system enhancements, and final behavior of the External Track & Trace system.

Over multiple iterations, the system was refined to improve:

Accuracy of status handling

XML compliance

Data consistency

Overall system reliability



---

2. Advanced Features


---

2.1 Idempotency (Controlled Data Sending)

The system ensures that the same status is not sent multiple times to Connexis.

Before sending data, the system verifies:

Whether the status has already been successfully processed

Whether a response has already been received



---

Behavior

Condition	System Action

Status already processed	Not sent again
Status pending or failed	Allowed to send



---

Benefit

Prevents duplicate updates

Maintains consistency across systems



---

2.2 Event-Level Tracking

The system tracks transactions at the event level, allowing detailed visibility of each step in the lifecycle.


---

Benefit

Better traceability

Improved debugging capability

Clear representation of transaction stages



---

2.3 Mapping-Driven Logic

The system uses a mapping table to control:

Status transformation

XML field values

Workflow behavior



---

Benefit

Reduces hardcoded logic

Enables easy configuration changes

Improves scalability



---

2.4 Multi-Product XML Support

The system dynamically generates XML structures based on product type.


---

Benefit

Supports multiple business flows

Ensures compatibility with different transaction types



---

2.5 Courier Integration

Courier-related details are integrated into the system to enhance tracking.


---

Included Data

Courier partner

Waybill number



---

Benefit

Enables tracking of physical documents

Improves end-to-end visibility



---

2.6 Automated Workflow Execution

The system uses a workflow engine to automate:

XML generation

File creation

Data transmission



---

Benefit

Reduces manual intervention

Ensures consistent execution



---

3. System Enhancements


---

3.1 Accurate Response Handling

The system ensures that responses received from Connexis are correctly interpreted and stored.


---

Improvement

Response values are consistently mapped to the correct system status

Ensures reliable retry and processing behavior



---

3.2 XML Compliance Improvement

The XML structure was refined to align with Connexis requirements.


---

Enhancement

Correct field naming and structure ensured

Improves successful integration with external systems



---

3.3 Customer Data Synchronization

The system ensures that customer-related data is always up to date.


---

Enhancement

Customer details are fetched dynamically from the referential system

Ensures accurate eligibility and processing



---

4. Edge Case Handling


---

4.1 Duplicate Data Prevention

Ensures that already processed statuses are not resent



---

4.2 Missing Mapping Handling

System stops execution if mapping is not available



---

4.3 No Response Scenario

Allows retry when no response is received



---

4.4 Reprocessing Scenarios

Prevents unnecessary re-sending when data is already processed



---

4.5 Data Validation Handling

Ensures only valid and properly structured data is sent



---

5. Final End-to-End Flow

Event Created → Validation → Mapping Evaluation → XML Generation → File Creation → Sending → Response Processing → Retry or Closure


---

